snippet.textDisplay:
Coke studio or no coke studio. Nothing can take away shine and depth from Shikwa and Jawab e Shikwa by Allama Iqbal. It remains to this day one of the best dialogues between the creator and the creation. Allama Iqbal was undoubtedly one the greatest social doctors Muslims ever got and the title Hakim ul Ummah perfectly fits this great man.
P. S. And the crux of entire Shikwa, Jawab e Shikwa perfectly potrays the personality of Iqbal:
Ki Muhammad (Saw) sai wafa tune toh hum tere hain
Yeh jahan cheez hain kya, loh wa qalam tere hain.....
